wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-62dce02 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"62dce02\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-large\">What can I do to prevent American cockroaches from infesting?<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-63eb967 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"63eb967\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">American cockroaches, also known as water bugs or palmetto bugs, are a common pest in many households. To prevent an infestation of these disgusting insects, removing any food sources they might be attracted to is essential. This means keeping kitchen counters and floors clean and free of crumbs or spills.<\/span><\/p><p>Another important step is to seal up any cracks or crevices in your home&#8217;s foundation or walls where the roaches might enter. American cockroaches are excellent climbers, so seal up windows and doors properly. Lastly, consider using insecticides around your home&#8217;s exterior perimeter and in areas like basements or crawl spaces where cockroaches tend to congregate.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-7f23e04 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"7f23e04\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element